content:
The Chat supervisor panel is your supervisors' one-stop shop for finding information about their organizations' chat buttons and chat agents. Make the Chat supervisor tab visible to users who are assigned to specified profiles.

Available in: Salesforce Classic, Performance Editions, Developer Edition orgs created after June 14, 2012, Unlimited Edition, and Enterprise Edition with Service Cloud.

To set tab visibility for Chat features: Manage Profiles and Permission Sets

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

From Setup, enter Profiles in the Quick Find box, then select Profiles.
Click Edit next to the profile that you want to give access to the supervisor tab.
Set the visibility of the Chat supervisor tab to Default On.
Click Save.
title: Setting Up Supervisor Tab Visibility for Service Cloud Chat
